<BaseLayout title="About & Editorial Policy" description="How Dama Korea researches, writes, updates and corrects its practical Korea guides."><section class="page-hero"><div class="shell"><span class="eyebrow">About Dama Korea</span><h1>Advice is useful only when you can see its limits.</h1><p>Dama Korea is an independent English-language guide for international visitors and residents. We explain practical decisions without pretending one answer fits every traveler.</p></div></section><article class="article-shell article-body legal-page">
  <h2>Our purpose</h2><p>We help people prepare for Korea, navigate a visit and understand the early steps of settling in. Our focus is the gap between a rule on an official page and the practical decision a reader still needs to make.</p>
  <h2>How we research</h2><p>Official agencies, transport operators, financial regulators and service providers are our starting point for rules and operational details. We compare those sources, identify where requirements vary and link readers back to the responsible organization for a final check.</p><p>Research, observation, interviews and first-hand experience are labeled rather than blended together. We do not invent a personal experience or use a fictional expert identity. A source link does not mean that organization endorses Dama Korea.</p>
  <h2>Time-sensitive information</h2><p>Guides show the date when their core information was last checked. Prices, schedules, visa rules, bank requirements and service conditions can change without notice. Readers should confirm critical information with the official source for their date and circumstances.</p>
  <h2>Corrections</h2><p>If a source has changed or a guide is unclear, email <a href="mailto:support@damaheritage.com?subject=Dama%20Korea%20correction">support@damaheritage.com</a>. Include the page URL, the statement in question and a source when possible. Material corrections will update the checked date or be noted in the article.</p>
  <h2>Commercial independence</h2><p>Advertising and future affiliate relationships help fund the site. They do not purchase favorable editorial conclusions. Affiliate links will be disclosed on the page where they appear, and readers will not pay more because a link is affiliated.</p>
  <h2>What we are not</h2><p>Dama Korea is not a government agency, law firm, financial adviser, immigration representative or medical provider. Our guides provide general educational information and cannot replace advice for an individual case.</p>
</article></BaseLayout>
